video.title: iCarly
video.synopsis: A cyberstar is born when 13-year-old Carly creates an Internet series with a little help from her best friend Sam and neighbor Freddie.

episodes.synopsis: Carly and Sam decide to host their talented classmates on their own online Web show, iCarly.
episodes.title: iPilot

episodes.synopsis: Carly has a crush on a boy named Jake and invites him to sing and play guitar on her Web show, learning too late that he is the world's worst singer.
episodes.title: iLike Jake

episodes.synopsis: Carly and Sam compete against Freddie and Spencer to see who can come up with the best plan to get more kids to watch the iCarly Webcast.
episodes.title: iWant More Viewers

episodes.synopsis: Carly, Sam and Freddie want their Web show to be reviewed by "Nevelocity," a really popular Website that reviews other sites and Webcasts.
episodes.title: iNevel

episodes.synopsis: Carly and Spencer's granddad makes a surprise visit. He's very concerned that Spencer is too irresponsible and wacky to be Carly's guardian.
episodes.title: iWanna Stay With Spencer

episodes.synopsis: Carly decides to do a Webcast showing what mean teachers do when they're not in school as she decides to follow her mean teacher, Miss Briggs.
episodes.title: iSpy a Mean Teacher

episodes.synopsis: Carly, Sam and Freddie try to break the world record for the longest continuous Webcast, while Spencer builds a giant sculpture downstairs.
episodes.title: iWant a World Record

episodes.synopsis: After Freddie begins filming his new girlfriend Valerie's own Web show, he finds himself torn between Valerie and best friends Carly, Spencer and Sam.
episodes.title: iWill Date Freddie

episodes.synopsis: Carly invites Spencer's hero, Harry Joyner, to look at Spencer's work. When Harry deems it amateurish, Spencer feels his life has lost its purpose.
episodes.title: iHeart Art

episodes.synopsis: iCarly's biggest fan, Mandy, is invited onto the show, but when she turns out to be more of a stalker than a fan, the kids have to get rid of her.
episodes.title: iAm Your Biggest Fan

episodes.synopsis: Carly and Sam set out to hatch chicks for a science project.
episodes.title: iHatch Chicks

episodes.synopsis: Carly makes Sam a one-of-a-kind iCarly shirt to honor their friendship, but when Sam trades the shirt for concert tickets, the two friends fight.
episodes.title: iDont Want to Fight

episodes.synopsis: iCarly asks fans to send in dance videos, and when more than 3,000 clips come in, Carly, Sam and Freddie try to stay up all night to watch them all.
episodes.title: iDream of Dance

episodes.synopsis: For Halloween, Carly does her Webcast in the supposedly haunted apartment 13B, and after numerous spooky things happen, the owners return early.
episodes.title: iScream on Halloween

episodes.synopsis: After saving the life of The Plain White T's lead singer, Spencer gets him to go on iCarly, but strange things start to happen during the Webcast.
episodes.title: iRue the Day

episodes.synopsis: Sam gets detention on the night of iCarly's 50th Web show spectacular.
episodes.title: iGot Detention

episodes.synopsis: Carly, Sam and Freddie are invited to Daka headquarters, where they are offered a large sum of money to endorse Daka's new shoe on iCarly.
episodes.title: iPromote Tech-Foots

episodes.synopsis: Carly gets a "B" on a history paper she should have gotten an "A" on.
episodes.title: iPromise Not to Tell

episodes.synopsis: A big-time producer wants to make iCarly into a TV show, but Carly, Sam and Freddie are upset to learn about the changes the producer wants to make.
episodes.title: iCarly Saves TV

episodes.synopsis: Sam gets a boyfriend, and the two are inseparable. But when the romance starts affecting iCarly, Carly and Freddie know they have to do something.
episodes.title: iHate Sam's Boyfriend

episodes.synopsis: After watching a segment on iCarly showing a man selling illegal copies of movies, two detectives use Carly and Spencer's loft for a stakeout.
episodes.title: iStakeout

episodes.synopsis: Carly learns that because of her Web show she's been given the opportunity for a full scholarship to the elite private school, Briarwood.
episodes.title: iMight Switch Schools

episodes.synopsis: Freddie joins Spencer in a fencing lesson, but things get complicated when Spencer gets him involved in a match with the amazing Doug Toder.
episodes.title: iFence

episodes.synopsis: Friend Gibby is too shy to ask out the girl he likes, so the gang makes him and his crush contestants in an "iWin a Date" segment on the Web show.
episodes.title: iWin a Date

episodes.synopsis: Mrs. Ackerman, the gang's teacher, goes through a rough breakup with her boyfriend, causing her to quarrel with her students.
episodes.title: iHave a Love Sick Teacher

episodes.synopsis: Freddie's new friend Shane makes quite an impression on Carly and Sam, who compete to get his attention. The rivalry starts to get out of hand.
episodes.title: iSaw Him First

episodes.synopsis: Spencer finds an old video game and quickly gets addicted to playing it instead of working. Meanwhile, Freddie refuses to forward a chain email.
episodes.title: iStage an Intervention

episodes.synopsis: Sam feels offended when Freddie claims she never pays him or Carly back. While Sam tries to get cash, Spencer helps a shy girl to impress her mother.
episodes.title: iOwe You

episodes.synopsis: Carly's doorman is hurt during a sketch, and while he recovers from his injuries, Freddie's mother gives him some tender loving care.
episodes.title: iHurt Lewbert

episodes.synopsis: Spencer, Carly and Sam bring Freddie to their favorite pie shop but are devastated to learn that the owner died, taking his recipe to the grave.
episodes.title: iPie

episodes.synopsis: In an attempt to spice up the Christmas tradition with an unconventional tree, Spencer accidentally sets fire to all of Carly's presents.
episodes.title: iChristmas

episodes.synopsis: Sam's pranks on Freddie go too far when she exposes that he's never kissed before. Everyone teases Freddie so relentlessly that he goes into hiding.
episodes.title: iKiss

episodes.synopsis: Carly offers a car as a prize for a contest. Unfortunately, the dealership that supposedly donated the vehicle doesn't know anything about it.
episodes.title: iGive Away a Car

episodes.synopsis: After Freddie confesses that he doesn't understand the appeal of Internet star Fred, Fred retaliates by instructing his fans to boycott "iCarly.
episodes.title: iMeet Fred

episodes.synopsis: Carly, Sam and Freddie score an invite to record a segment at a mixed martial arts event. Spencer won't let them go, so the friends plan to dupe him.
episodes.title: iLook Alike

episodes.synopsis: During Green Week, Carly's earth science teacher instructs the class to create environmentally friendly inventions. Carly's first project is a total flop, and her second attempt leads to a run-in with the FBI at the Groovy Smoothie. Whoops!
episodes.title: i Go Nuclear

episodes.synopsis: The "iCarly" gang backs David Archuleta during the "America Sings" competition but feels sorry for his rival after learning about his mom's illness.
episodes.title: iRocked the Vote

episodes.synopsis: Sam's got a crush on a boy at school. The trouble is, he likes only the really girly girls, so Sam needs a makeover, and who better to help than Carly? Meanwhile, Spencer's convinced that a girl is more interested in his tuxedo than what's in it.
episodes.title: iMake Sam Girlier

episodes.synopsis: When Carly's old pal Missy Robinson returns to Seattle, Sam's convinced the new girl in town is out to sabotage her friendship with Carly. Meanwhile, a vengeful neighbor gets even with Spencer by refusing to rescue him from a locked basement.
episodes.title: iReunite with Missy

episodes.synopsis: When Carly loses her domain name, her number-one fan comes to the rescue until iCarly.com falls into the scheming hands of none other than Nevel.
episodes.title: iWant My Website Back

episodes.synopsis: The best locker in school is up for grabs, and a contest will determine who gets to move in. But when Sam and Freddie tie for the prize, they're forced to share the locker, and nobody wins. Meanwhile, Carly takes art classes at the community center.
episodes.title: iMust Have Locker 239

episodes.synopsis: Carly, Sam and Freddie present iCarly Awards for best user-generated content, while Spencer enlists swimsuit models to make the awards statuettes.
episodes.title: iCarly Awards

episodes.synopsis: Sam tells Freddie that she has a twin sister named Melanie, but he's not buying it and sets out to prove that Melanie is just Sam in disguise. Meanwhile, Spencer plots to take down his nemesis, Chuck, who's enlisted Carly's help as a math tutor.
episodes.title: iTwins

episodes.synopsis: Carly is very concerned that the Los Angeles-based Dingo channel might be copying "iCarly's" material, so she and best friends Sam and Freddie head off to sunny California to figure out what's going on.
episodes.title: iTake on Dingo

episodes.synopsis: When Sam accidentally reveals to Carly that she and Freddie shared a secret kiss, Carly confronts them both about why they never told her about it.
episodes.title: iThink They Kissed

episodes.synopsis: When Carly, Sam and Freddie defeat a famous television chef in a cooking challenge, the chef quits his show and refuses to come out of his bedroom.
episodes.title: iCook

episodes.synopsis: When Carly, Sam and Freddie accidentally get Principal Franklin fired, Miss Briggs and Mr. Howard take control and enforce harsh rules.
episodes.title: iHave My Principals

episodes.synopsis: So many boys show up for a "take Carly to the dance contest" that Carly, Sam and Freddie have to hold a speed-dating session to meet them all.
episodes.title: iSpeed Date

episodes.synopsis: When Carly, Sam and Freddie agree to make a music video for a pop star's comeback, they discover that the pop star is out of shape and untalented.
episodes.title: iFix a Pop Star

episodes.synopsis: When Freddie saves Carly's life, Carly falls in love with him. Meanwhile, Sam and Spencer compete against each other in a paintball game.
episodes.title: iSaved Your Life

episodes.synopsis: When Gibby discovers Freddie with his girlfriend, he vows revenge. Meanwhile, Spencer's career takes off when the paper incorrectly reports his death.
episodes.title: iEnrage Gibby

episodes.synopsis: When the gang discovers that Lewbert was once a happy young man engaged to a beautiful woman, they set out to reunite the lost lovers.
episodes.title: iFind Lewbert's Lost Love

episodes.synopsis: Sam reveals to Carly and Freddie that she used to compete in pageants as a young girl, and she asks Carly to compete against her long-time rival.
episodes.title: iWas a Pageant Girl

episodes.synopsis: When Sam ends up in jail, Carly and Freddie vow that the Web show must go on. They try to enlist Spencer's help, but he has a date he can't cancel.
episodes.title: iWon't Cancel the Show

episodes.synopsis: A billionaire asks the gang to perform the first live Web show from outer space, and they are tested to make sure they can handle the tough journey.
episodes.title: iSpace Out

episodes.synopsis: After an expert validates fuzzy footage of Bigfoot on the Web show, Carly convinces the gang to take Socko's RV upstate and join the search.
episodes.title: iBelieve in Bigfoot

episodes.synopsis: Fed up with his mom treating him like a baby, Freddie moves out. The gang starts a pet photography business, but they end up feuding with a rival.
episodes.title: iMove Out

episodes.synopsis: When a heat wave causes a power outage, Spencer saves the day with a Norwegian air conditioner. Word spreads, and he and Carly are swamped by guests.
episodes.title: iBeat the Heat

episodes.synopsis: The cast introduces exclusive, never-before-seen bloopers and outtakes from the entire series' run.
episodes.title: iBloop

episodes.synopsis: The iCarly gang makes a detour on the way to a web conference to help a lonely fan on her birthday, but the crazy fan causes their plans to go awry.
episodes.title: iPsycho

episodes.synopsis: After a stand-up comedy video project causes dissension between them, Carly and Sam split their creative partnership and friendship.
episodes.title: iQuit iCarly

episodes.synopsis: In jest, Carly issues a challenge to martial arts expert Shelby Marx, who agrees to square off with Carly in a friendly charity match. But when Nevel's shenanigans get Shelby's blood boiling, it looks like Carly might be cruisin' for a bruisin'.
episodes.title: iFight Shelby Marx

episodes.synopsis: Spencer's not thrilled when his sis starts dating a rebel, but Carly learns a secret about the bad boy that convinces her he's getting a bad rap. Meanwhile, Sam and Freddie post some seriously icky videos online.
episodes.title: iDate a Bad Boy

episodes.synopsis: Carly, Sam and Freddie are thrilled to be going to Japan to attend the iWeb Awards. But they may not survive their flight and their rivals' antics.
episodes.title: iGo to Japan
